## As a design leader – be ready to talk numbers

**Goal:** Articulate how design moves key metrics.

Impact stories to prepare:
- Reduced support cases or handling time via clearer IA, flows, and in‑product education.
- Increased revenue metrics (conversion, expansion, retention) via UX improvements and experiments.
- Higher engagement (task completion, adoption, usage depth) tied to specific design changes.
- Reduced rework, fewer abandoned features, faster cycles through better discovery and validation.

Reference:
- [Made to measure: Getting design leadership metrics right – McKinsey](https://www.mckinsey.com/capabilities/tech-and-ai/our-insights/made-to-measure-getting-design-leadership-metrics-right)


