## Philosophy

Use this as “Operating principles for my leadership.”

### Protect design integrity

- Advocate for coherent end‑to‑end experiences, not isolated features.
- Protect user trust: clarity, consent, explainability, and privacy—especially in AI‑heavy products.

### User research as a scientific process

- Hypothesis‑driven: define questions, hypotheses, and decisions up front.
- Method‑fit: choose qualitative, quantitative, or mixed methods based on the decision to be made.
- Treat research as a continuous practice, not a one‑off phase.

References:
- [Types of user research methods – User Interviews](https://www.userinterviews.com/ux-research-field-guide-chapter/user-research-types)
- (Browse) [Research methods topic – Nielsen Norman Group](https://www.nngroup.com/topic/research-methods/)

### Ambient AI design

- Design AI that works in the background, minimizes cognitive load, and is easy to inspect, override, and correct.
- Make data use, triggers, and model behavior legible; avoid “magic” that erodes trust.

Reference:
- [Ambient Intelligence – AI UX Design Patterns](https://www.aiuxdesign.guide/patterns/ambient-intelligence)


